import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['delay'] = pd.to_datetime(data['delay'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='mean')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='distance', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['distance'].median(), color='red', label='Median distance: {:.2f}'.format(data['distance'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight distances?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['hour'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce').dt.hour
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='hour', y='delay', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['delay'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median Delay: {:.2f}'.format(data['delay'].median()))
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('How does time of day affect flight delays?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['distance_range'] = data['distance_range'].astype('category')
    data = data.sort_values(by='distance_range')
    chart = sns.barplot(x='distance_range', y='distance', data=data, ci=None)
    chart.set_title('What is the distribution of flight distances by distance range?', wrap=True)
    chart.set_xlabel('Distance Range')
    chart.set_ylabel('Distance')
    chart.axhline(y=data['distance'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median Distance: {:.2f}'.format(data['distance'].median()))
    chart.legend()
    return chart

chart = plot(data)
